12/05/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Friendship and co-operation between Turkey and the United States will continue, according to US Ambassador to Turkey Robert Pearson.
In an interview with the newspaper <I>Hurriyet</I> on Sunday (11 May), Pearson said that co-operative efforts to rebuild Iraq would help mend any problems in relations between the two countries.
Furthermore, he suggested that Turkey support the US call to lift sanctions on Iraq.
Also Sunday, Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said that Washington has traditionally been Turkey's strategic ally and will continue to hold this position.
(Hurriyet - 12/05/03;
Anadolu Agency, NTV - 11/05/03)
